{"_id":"Tx530KqLftu35dst","name":"Cartographer","permission":{"default":0,"oGHR2KXa4ft7ui9d":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.ZXCChFwzf8it6ef5"}},"content":"<p><strong><img style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block; border: none;\" src=\"modules/cartagropher-career/icons/cartographer.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></strong></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Cartographer Advance Scheme</h2>\n<p><strong>Symbol</strong>: Sextant, Compass or Cardinal star&nbsp;</p>\n <p><strong>Societies</strong>: The Cartographers' Guild&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Saying</strong>: Horror vacui - fear of emptiness&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Study</strong>: Map projections, Generalization, Symbology, Composition, Typography, Layout&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Titles</strong>: Explorer, Pathfinder, Trailblazer, or Cartographer&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Hmm... What an interesting anomoly. The details of the coastline suggest an inlet along this stretch. Perhaps we could land there and I could map out the interior?</em> <p>Astromancers are experts in interpretation of heavenly movements, augury, dreams, and haruspicy, using the Blue Wind to divine omens from them. They dress in dark blue, bedecked with jewelry such as pendants, rings, and earrings, which they can easily afford due to the generous payments they receive for their work. They tend to know when people are about to speak, but not what they say. Despite this, they enjoy the reputation of knowing what everyone else could not.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Cartographers chart the lay of the land for rich patrons, hardy explorers, and collectors. They accompany expeditions into the wild but also transpose the shoddy work of others into a more readable form. Maps in the Old World are notoriously unreliable â€“ whether they are surveys of local trails, ambitious region wide guides, or the mainly fictional representations of the Old World itself. Yet the services of Cartographers are still in great demand.&nbsp;